OVERVIEW:
Galactic Fleet Command military ranking system with 18 progressive ranks from Recruit to Fleet Admiral, earned through combat prowess, economic achievement, territorial control, and galactic contributions. Ranks permanent, displayed prominently, provide trading bonuses and special privileges.

FACTS:
* 18 military ranks across 5 tiers: Enlisted (3), NCO (3), Warrant (2), Officer (5), Flag (5)
* Ranks earned through achievements, never lost
* Trading bonuses: +2% to +50% based on rank
* Visible to all players (profile, leaderboards, team rosters)
* Requirements: credits earned, sectors visited, trades, combat victories, planets owned, faction missions
* Special medals for extraordinary achievements beyond ranks
* Fleet Admiral: <0.01% of players expected to achieve
* Rank benefits include diplomatic immunity, governance roles, galactic policy influence

TERMINOLOGY:
* Military Rank: Achievement-based progression system reflecting player accomplishments
* Trading Bonus: Percentage reduction in buy prices and increase in sell prices
* Faction Reputation Gain: Bonus multiplier to faction standing increases
* Diplomatic Immunity: Protection from attacks in allied territories
* Fleet Coordination: Ability to lead multi-ship operations
* Legendary Status: Recognition that affects NPC behavior and port greetings
* Insignia: Visual rank indicator displayed with player name

ENLISTED_RANKS:
